title: Grateful Dead Live at Shoreline Amphitheatre on 1993-05-21
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi CR-7A) > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.8 MHz) >KORG AudioGate 4 > Samplitude Pro X3 Suite > FLAC/24
description:
Set 1

Let The Good Times Roll, Feel Like A Stranger, Friend Of The Devil, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, West L.A. Fadeaway, Eternity, Liberty

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Way To Go Home, Estimated Prophet-> He's Gone-> Jam-> Drums-> Jam-> All Along The Watchtower, Morning Dew, E:Baba O'Riley-> E: Tomorrow Never Knows

reviews.review_text:
Mixed bag.  The mix has none of Bob's guitar until well towards end of first set. FOTD has some very unique moments and soloing for the period. Liberty fits well as first set closer. 
The jam in China Rider never hits the climax. Jerry throws down and interesting overdriven guitar intro to Way To Go Home. Jerry drops a clam in Estimated and goes to the G-C chorus change when he should have stuck on the verse F#min until Bob was done with next line of verse. The last 10 seconds of Estimated I swear Jerry teases 'Love Scene' from Zabriskie Point. A strong post space. After Vegas me and my buddy were sitting in a car in San Diego listening to GD hour and we both just turned to each other and said 'let's drive to shoreline.' We got in this night and drove back next day.
